WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
Welcome to Intro to Derivatives.

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:12.000
The derivative measures the slope of a tangent line to a curve at a point.

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:20.000
We define it as the limit of the difference quotient as h approaches zero.

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:28.000
Basic rules: the power rule, product rule, and chain rule simplify differentiation.

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:35.000
For example, the derivative of x squared is 2x.
